# EC2 module

This Terraform module provisions a single **Amazon EC2** instance with secure defaults (encrypted root volume, IMDSv2), optional extra EBS volumes, and optional IAM instance profile attachment.

For **Google Compute Engine**, see `Gcp/ComputeEngine`. For **Azure**, see `Azure/VirtualMachine`.

## Features

- One **`aws_instance`** with configurable AMI, type, subnet, and security groups
- **Root volume** — size, type, encryption, optional KMS
- **Optional extra EBS** volumes + attachments with explicit **device names**
- **Metadata** — configurable `http_tokens` (default `required` for IMDSv2)
- **Tags** — `Name`, `environment`, `managed_by` merged with your tags

## Usage

### Call from another repository

```hcl
module "ec2" {
  source = "git::https://github.com/saurabhrsahu/terraform-modules.git//Aws/EC2?ref=main"
  # ...
}
```

Configure the **AWS** provider in the root module; this module only pins `hashicorp/aws`.

```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = ">= 5.0.0, < 6.0.0"
    }
  }
}

provider "aws" {
  region = var.region
}
```

### Basic usage

```hcl
module "app" {
  source = "../../modules/Aws/EC2"

  instance_name = "app-01"
  ami           = "ami-0abcdef1234567890" # use a current AMI in your region
  instance_type = "t3.small"
  subnet_id     = "subnet-0abc..."
  vpc_security_group_ids = ["sg-0abc..."]

  associate_public_ip_address = false
  key_name                    = "my-keypair"

  environment = "dev"
  tags = {
    app = "api"
  }
}
```

### Extra EBS volumes

```hcl
  ebs_volumes = {
    data = {
      device_name = "/dev/sdf"
      size        = 100
      volume_type = "gp3"
    }
  }
```

On **Nitro** instances, OS device names may appear as `/dev/nvme*` — pick devices per [AWS device naming](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/nvme-ebs-volumes.html).

## Inputs

| Name | Description | Type | Default | Required |
|------|-------------|------|---------|:--------:|
| `instance_name` | Name tag | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `ami` | AMI ID | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `instance_type` | Instance type | `string` | `"t3.micro"` | no |
| `subnet_id` | Subnet ID | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `vpc_security_group_ids` | Security group IDs | `list(string)` | n/a | yes |
| `key_name` | EC2 Key Pair name | `string` | `null` | no |
| `associate_public_ip_address` | Assign public IPv4 | `bool` | `false` | no |
| `user_data` | User data script | `string` | `null` | no |
| `iam_instance_profile_name` | IAM instance **profile** name | `string` | `null` | no |
| `root_volume_size` | Root size (GB) | `number` | `30` | no |
| `root_volume_type` | Root EBS type | `string` | `"gp3"` | no |
| `root_volume_encrypted` | Encrypt root volume | `bool` | `true` | no |
| `root_volume_kms_key_id` | Root KMS key | `string` | `null` | no |
| `metadata_http_tokens` | IMDSv2: optional / required / disabled | `string` | `"required"` | no |
| `ebs_volumes` | Map of extra volumes (see variable type) | `map(object)` | `{}` | no |
| `enable_monitoring` | Detailed CloudWatch monitoring | `bool` | `false` | no |
| `environment` | dev / stage / prod | `string` | `"dev"` | no |
| `tags` | Extra tags | `map(string)` | `{}` | no |

## Outputs

| Name | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `instance_id` | Instance ID |
| `instance_arn` | Instance ARN |
| `private_ip` | Private IP |
| `public_ip` | Public IP (if assigned) |
| `availability_zone` | AZ |
| `summary` | Short summary |
| `connection_info` | Example SSH line |

## Requirements

| Name | Version |
|------|---------|
| terraform | >= 1.3.0 |
| aws | >= 5.0.0, < 6.0.0 |
